Passkey / Phone Authentication Plan
Status:
- Planned, not implemented yet.
- Admin only for now.
- Do not add to Customerlogin, Technicianlogin, or Storelogin yet.

Goal:
- Admin logs in once with username/password.
- Inside admin profile/settings, admin clicks Setup Passkey.
- Browser/phone asks Face ID, fingerprint, device PIN, Windows Hello, or Android screen lock.
- Passkey is saved for that admin user.
- Next time on /Adminlogin, admin can click Login with Passkey.
- Backend verifies WebAuthn and creates the normal auth_token JWT cookie.
- Existing role redirect sends admin to /Admindashboard.
- If passkey fails, username/password login must still work.

Important security meaning:
- Do not build custom face recognition.
- Do not open camera.
- Do not store face data.
- Do not store fingerprint data.
- Do not store device PIN.
- Do not store private key.
- Store only public key credential data from WebAuthn.
- Use the phone/laptop operating system authenticator through Passkeys/WebAuthn.

Required packages:
- @simplewebauthn/server
- @simplewebauthn/browser

Production Vercel passkey config:
- WEBAUTHN_RP_NAME=Amardip Lifts ERP
- WEBAUTHN_RP_ID=amardip-erp.vercel.app
- WEBAUTHN_ORIGIN=https://amardip-erp.vercel.app

Passkey domain rules:
- This project is not using a custom domain.
- Stable production admin login URL is https://amardip-erp.vercel.app/Adminlogin.
- RP_ID must be only amardip-erp.vercel.app.
- ORIGIN must be only https://amardip-erp.vercel.app.
- Do not put /Adminlogin in RP_ID or ORIGIN.
- Do not use random Vercel preview URLs for passkey registration/login.
- If domain changes later, passkeys may need to be registered again.

Planned WebAuthn config file:
- lib/webauthnConfig.js

Expected exports:
- rpName from WEBAUTHN_RP_NAME or Amardip Lifts ERP.
- rpID from WEBAUTHN_RP_ID or amardip-erp.vercel.app.
- origin from WEBAUTHN_ORIGIN or https://amardip-erp.vercel.app.
- Localhost fallback only when NODE_ENV is not production.

Planned DB helper:
- lib/passkeys.js

Planned helper functions:
- ensurePasskeyTables
- saveChallenge
- getValidChallenge
- deleteChallenge
- deleteExpiredChallenges
- getUserPasskeys
- getPasskeyByCredentialId
- saveUserPasskey
